The paper deals with constructing and analyzing multiple-description codes, which are typically used in information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. The use of lattice vector quantization is also relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper may have applications in computer vision (cs.CV) for image and video coding.
